* **Anti-Debugging & Tampering Checks (`a0nt`, `a0nE`, `a0nd`):** The script checks the environment. It inspects its own functions (using `.toString()`) to see if they've been formatted or modified. If it detects Chrome DevTools or tampering, it will trigger an infinite loop of `debugger;` statements or intentionally crash the script using infinite RegEx evaluations.

